metadata.name: Hermaphrodite of Sin
metadata.description:
This piece tries to explain "choiced point of view" towards queer orientations in eyes of society and religion. Look at it: an absurd representation of reality which isn't reality itself at all. It is awful to be victim of this gross point of view. By channelling this feeling, I have tried to express how it is important to be mighty: It is extremely crucial to be on our way of living, no matter who says what.
In my Egon Schiele Tarot deck, this piece represent Devil Card.
